The article discusses the importance of rural America's success for the overall success of the country. The author highlights the efforts made by the current administration to invest in rural infrastructure and rebuild rural communities. The American Rescue Plan and the Bipartisan Infrastructure Law are mentioned as initiatives that aim to provide resources and support for rural families and communities. The article also emphasizes the significance of strong infrastructure in rural areas, as it contributes to job creation, economic growth, and lower prices. The administration announces the launch of a rural infrastructure tour, where cabinet members and senior officials will visit rural communities to deliver infrastructure investments and listen to their needs. Overall, the article emphasizes the commitment of the administration to improve the lives of rural Americans and create opportunities for a better future.